Container Lifestyle
=creation
docker container run – t -I -d <image name:tag name>
-t = terminal
-I = interactive
-d = detach mode 

=Check or List:
Docker container ls ( Docker will display only running containers)
Docker container ls -a  (this command display all containers both stopped & running)
Docker container ls -l ( this will show you last created container)
Docker container ls -q ( this will display the short ids for all running containers)
Docker container ls -aq ( this will display the short ids for all running & stopped containers)

=Stop/start
Docker container stop <container-name>
Docker container start <container-name>

=  Name to a container
Docker container run -itd –name <name> <image name:tag name>

=  Rename a container
Docker container rename  <old container name> <new container name >

=  Login inside a container
Docker container exec -it <container-name> /bin/bash   ( or /bin/sh)
Exit

=  Logs
Docker container logs  < container name >
Docker container logs --help


One docker host contains 100 containers, got alert for high memory issues. So now need to check which container having high utilization but checking manually for 100 containers are nearly impossible and time consume. 

=  Stats
Docker container stats

= inspect (Details about Container)
Docker container inspect < container name >

=  Decom : Stop and Remove
Docker container stop < container name >
Docker container rm < container name >
